The paper deals with author name disambiguation, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and databases (DB). The use of clustering methods and blocking functions also suggests a connection to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). The mention of computation time reduction and parallelization indicates a possible link to data structures (DS) and algorithms (AI).
